## What are Python conditionals?
A conditional statement is used to handle conditions in your program. These statements guide the control structure
of a program while making decisions based on the conditions encountered by throughout the programs execution.

## If…else…
One of the most popular control structures in Python is the if…elif…else… statement. This is what is known as a
selection control structure where the outcome of the program is based on the condition met.

## Indentation
Where other programming languages rely on curly braces, Python relies on indentation to define scope. If you omit
the indentation when it is required, your code will not execute correctly.

# if…elif…else syntax
if expression1:
    statement(s)
elif expression2:
    statement(s)
elif expression3:
    statement(s)
else:
    statement(s)